{
  "texts": [
    "However, since the support and confidence for association rules are not significant due to the small sample size, we consider all the \"strong\" rules with non-zero support and confidence scores for those labels.",
    "The rules we consider have the form: (strong-label → weak-label), where the weak label (such as Anhedonia, Fatigue, Indecisiveness, and Retardation) means the labels for which our model achieves either 0 F1 score or very low recall, i.e., less or equal to chance level.",
    "These are the candidate labels for which we would like to have increased accuracy.",
    "On the other hand, strong labels are those for which we have at least a good recall, i.e., beyond chance level.",
    "By emphasizing high recall, we intend to prevent a depression symptom from being undetected by our model."
  ]
}